{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"witted-mycologic-robberfly","description":"## Why\nIncident 2731: autodeploy's failing rebuild loop churned multi-GB buildkit layers on the 30G root disk; `docker image prune -f` runs only on the success path (autodeploy.sh:166), so failed-loop garbage accumulated until transient ENOSPC fail-closed live reviews.\n## What\nRun image + builder prune (e.g. `docker builder prune -f --keep-storage` cap or `--filter until=72h`) on the failure path of infra/scripts/autodeploy.sh as well.\n## Scope\n- infra/scripts/autodeploy.sh only; keep the success-path prune.\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A failed deploy attempt leaves bounded build-cache growth (prune executed on failure path).\n- [ ] Success path behavior unchanged.\n- [ ] Unit/shell test or documented manual verification of both paths.","id":"e2c5-f09b-cea2-4d9b","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"autodeploy: prune docker build cache on the failure path (disk-pressure hardening)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783658976831400001,"uuid":"c1956f84-336d-45bc-9163-c6c705fa4414"}